snippet.textDisplay: This 2018-2019 season was magical during the regular season. Not many years that we've gone 14-2 let alone go on a 12 week winning streak. The success of anyone or anything naturally will attract haters who want to see others fail. I get they're memes and all, but some are just plain hate. I don't mind them, this message is mainly for the Ravens organization and the fans. I am aware that the Ravens probably won't see this, but for the fans like me, keep your head up. Listen to the speech Ray Lewis did after the AFC Championship loss in 2011 to the Patriots and let it inspire you to look forward to next season. Call me emotional or what ever, but i love this sport and i love the Ravens. Like almost everyone else, i don't like seeing my team lose. Nor do i like seeing our players feel bad. But again let Ray Lewis motivate you to keep your head up https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zp0ABHaFwMY

snippet.textDisplay:
As a 9er fan watching game without any biased for either team....I will say the Ravens as well as Lamar Jackson choked (2 INT's, fumble and failure to convert 4th downs), this is now two playoff games where he has played bad (including last year's playoff game). Most of Lamar's passing and rushing yards came in garbage time when Tennessee defense was playing soft/prevent. If any other QB, including Jimmy G, played as bad the headlines and narrative from national media, especially the NFL network media crew, would have been, "Jimmy G chokes again" in big game.
When Lamar was tearing it up, everyone praised him and how great he was as a QB (and it was deserved) but now the national media should also point out his bad game, like they would if it was Jimmy G, Kirk Cousins or any other QB who might have choked.
